items.description:
As a new patient, there typically isn’t enough time during the first visit to collect all the necessary medical history and also complete a thorough full skin exam. That’s why we schedule the Full Skin Exam as a follow-up visit. Are there any specific concerns—like acne, rosacea, or a spot you're worried about—that we can address during the first visit? I’d be happy to schedule both appointments for you today so we can get everything set up in advance.


Also adding: We start by scheduling a focused dermatology visit to establish care. This allows the provider enough time to gather your full medical history and understand your skin concerns before doing a comprehensive full skin exam.
